---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import RelatedServices from '../../../components/RelatedServices.astro';
import CrossSiloLinks from '../../../components/CrossSiloLinks.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Technical Translation Dubai | MOJ Certified"
  description="Expert technical translation in Dubai. Engineering specifications, user manuals, safety documentation, and technical drawings. Industry-certified translators."
>
  <section class="hero-section bg-dark" data-theme="dark">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">HOME</a>
        <span class="separator">&gt;</span>
        <a href="/specialized-translation/">SPECIALIZED</a>
        <span class="separator">&gt;</span>
        <span class="current">TECHNICAL</span>
      </nav>

      <h1>Technical Translation Services in Dubai</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Engineering & Industrial Documentation</p>
      <p class="hero-intro">Technical documents demand precision. A mistranslated specification can lead to equipment failure, safety incidents, or project delays. Our technical translators combine language expertise with engineering knowledge to deliver <a href="/services/legal-translation/">MOJ-certified translations</a> that industry professionals trust.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Technical Documents We Translate</h2>

      <div class="tech-grid">
        <div class="tech-card">
          <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i>
          <h3>Engineering Specifications</h3>
          <p>Technical specs, design documents, and engineering standards</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-card">
          <i class="fas fa-book-open"></i>
          <h3>User Manuals</h3>
          <p>Operation guides, instruction manuals, and quick-start guides</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-card">
          <i class="fas fa-hard-hat"></i>
          <h3>Safety Documentation</h3>
          <p>HSE documents, safety data sheets, and compliance materials</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-card">
          <i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i>
          <h3>Technical Drawings</h3>
          <p>CAD annotations, blueprints, and schematic labels</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-card">
          <i class="fas fa-clipboard-check"></i>
          <h3>Quality Documents</h3>
          <p>ISO procedures, quality manuals, and inspection reports</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-card">
          <i class="fas fa-wrench"></i>
          <h3>Maintenance Guides</h3>
          <p>Service manuals, repair procedures, and maintenance schedules</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Industries We Serve</h2>

      <div class="industry-grid">
        <div class="industry-item">
          <i class="fas fa-oil-can"></i>
          <span>Oil & Gas</span>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-item">
          <i class="fas fa-building"></i>
          <span>Construction</span>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-item">
          <i class="fas fa-industry"></i>
          <span>Manufacturing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-item">
          <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i>
          <span>Power & Energy</span>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-item">
          <i class="fas fa-plane"></i>
          <span>Aviation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-item">
          <i class="fas fa-ship"></i>
          <span>Maritime</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What You Need to Know About Technical Translation</h2>

      <h3>The Real Question: Will the Engineer Build It Right?</h3>
      <p>Technical translation is not about linguistic elegance. It is about ensuring an engineer in Dubai can read specifications from Germany, Japan, or the US and build exactly what the designer intended. One mistranslated measurement, one unclear material specification, one ambiguous safety instruction can cause equipment failure, project delays, or worse.</p>

      <p>This is why we use translators with engineering backgrounds. They understand context. They know that "tolerance" in manufacturing is not the same as "tolerance" in everyday language. They recognize when a term has different meanings in different industries.</p>

      <h3>Oil and Gas Industry Requirements</h3>
      <p>The UAE's oil and gas sector has specific documentation needs:</p>

      <div class="comparison-box">
        <div class="comparison-col">
          <h4>Upstream Documentation</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Drilling specifications</li>
            <li>Well completion reports</li>
            <li>Reservoir studies</li>
            <li>Seismic survey data</li>
            <li>Production reports</li>
            <li>HSE procedures</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="comparison-col">
          <h4>Downstream Documentation</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Refinery process manuals</li>
            <li>Pipeline specifications</li>
            <li>Storage facility procedures</li>
            <li>Safety data sheets (SDS)</li>
            <li>Maintenance schedules</li>
            <li>Emergency response plans</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Construction and Engineering</h3>
      <p>Dubai's construction industry relies on accurate technical documentation:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Structural specifications:</strong> Load calculations, reinforcement details, material grades</li>
        <li><strong>MEP documentation:</strong> Mechanical, electrical, plumbing system specifications</li>
        <li><strong>Fire and life safety:</strong> Dubai Civil Defence requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Quality control:</strong> Inspection reports, test certificates</li>
        <li><strong>As-built drawings:</strong> Final construction documentation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Manufacturing and Industrial</h3>

      <div class="process-breakdown">
        <h4>User Manuals</h4>
        <p>Equipment operators need clear instructions. Our translations maintain the step-by-step structure while ensuring safety warnings are prominent and unambiguous.</p>

        <h4>Maintenance Guides</h4>
        <p>Service technicians rely on accurate maintenance schedules, torque specifications, and lubrication requirements. We preserve technical precision.</p>

        <h4>Quality Procedures</h4>
        <p>ISO 9001, ISO 14001, and other quality management system documentation requires consistent terminology across the entire document set.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Safety Documentation: No Margin for Error</h3>
      <p>Safety-critical documentation demands absolute precision:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Safety Data Sheets (SDS):</strong> Hazard classifications, handling procedures, emergency measures</li>
        <li><strong>HAZOP studies:</strong> Hazard and operability analysis for process industries</li>
        <li><strong>Work permits:</strong> Hot work, confined space, height work authorizations</li>
        <li><strong>PPE requirements:</strong> Personal protective equipment specifications</li>
        <li><strong>Emergency procedures:</strong> Evacuation plans, first aid, spill response</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Common Technical Translation Mistakes</h3>

      <div class="mistake-list">
        <div class="mistake-item">
          <span class="mistake-icon">✗</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Unit conversion errors:</strong> Mixing metric and imperial without clear indication
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mistake-item">
          <span class="mistake-icon">✗</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Material grade ambiguity:</strong> Steel grades, alloy specifications must be exact
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mistake-item">
          <span class="mistake-icon">✗</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Tolerance misinterpretation:</strong> ±0.01mm is not the same as ±0.1mm
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mistake-item">
          <span class="mistake-icon">✗</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Softened safety warnings:</strong> "Must" becoming "should" reduces urgency
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>CAD and Technical Drawings</h3>
      <p>We handle text elements within technical drawings:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Dimension annotations</li>
        <li>Part labels and bill of materials</li>
        <li>Title blocks and revision notes</li>
        <li>Assembly instructions</li>
        <li>Weld symbols and surface finish notes</li>
      </ul>

      <p>We can work with exported text from CAD files or translate directly on PDF drawings.</p>

      <h3>Regulatory Submissions</h3>
      <p>Technical documents often need translation for regulatory approval:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Dubai Municipality building permits</li>
        <li>Civil Defence approvals</li>
        <li>DEWA connection applications</li>
        <li>Free zone authority submissions</li>
        <li>Environmental impact assessments</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Realistic Timeline</h3>
      <p>Standard technical manuals (20-50 pages) take 2-3 days. Large documentation sets (equipment manuals, 100+ pages) may need a week. Safety-critical documentation gets priority handling. If you have a project deadline or regulatory submission date, tell us when you upload.</p>

      <div class="info-callout">
        <h4><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Terminology Consistency</h4>
        <p>For large documentation projects, we create terminology glossaries at the start. This ensures the same term is translated the same way throughout all documents. Consistency matters when multiple technicians use the same documentation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <RelatedServices
        pageKey="technical"
        title="You May Also Need"
        showFamily={true}
        showPrerequisites={true}
        showNextSteps={true}
        showCrossSilo={true}
        maxItems={8}
      />
      <CrossSiloLinks maxLinks={6} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-primary">
    <div class="container cta-section">
      <h2>Need Technical Translation?</h2>
      <p>Send your technical documents via WhatsApp. We'll assess complexity and assign the right subject matter expert.</p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="https://wa.me/971508620217?text=I%20need%20technical%20translation" class="btn btn-accent">
          <i class="fab fa-whatsapp"></i> Send Documents
        </a>
        <a href="/specialized-translation/" class="btn btn-outline">
          <i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> All Specialized Services
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-section { padding: 8rem 0 4rem; background: var(--primary-color); }
  .breadcrumb { font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .breadcrumb a { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: none; }
  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: #fff; }
  .breadcrumb .separator { margin: 0 0.75rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4); }
  .breadcrumb .current { color: #fff; }
  h1 { font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #fff; }
  .hero-subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--accent-color); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  .hero-intro { font-size: 1.1rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); max-width: 800px; line-height: 1.8; }
  .section { padding: 5rem 0; }
  .section h2 { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--primary-color); }
  .tech-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 2rem; }
  .tech-card { text-align: center; padding: 2rem; background: var(--bg-light); border-radius: 12px; }
  .tech-card i { font-size: 2.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .tech-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: var(--primary-color); }
  .tech-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .industry-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem; }
  .industry-item { background: #fff; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; text-align: center; box-shadow: 0 2px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05); }
  .industry-item i { font-size: 2rem; color: var(--accent-color); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block; }
  .industry-item span { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--primary-color); font-weight: 600; }
  .bg-primary { background: var(--primary-color); }
  .bg-primary h2, .bg-primary p { color: #fff; }
  .cta-section { text-align: center; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .cta-section p { opacity: 0.9; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-accent { background: var(--accent-color); color: #fff; }
  .btn-outline { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); }
  @media (max-width: 992px) { .tech-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } .industry-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { h1 { font-size: 2rem; } .tech-grid, .industry-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .hero-section { padding: 6rem 0 3rem; } }

  /* Content section styles */
  .comparison-box {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .comparison-col {
    background: var(--bg-light);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .comparison-col h4 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent-color);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .comparison-col ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .comparison-col li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .process-breakdown {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8f9fa 0%, #e9ecef 100%);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color);
  }

  .process-breakdown h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }

  .process-breakdown h4:not(:first-child) {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .process-breakdown p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .mistake-list {
    background: #fff5f5;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .mistake-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }

  .mistake-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .mistake-item:first-child {
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .mistake-icon {
    color: #dc3545;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .info-callout {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8f4f8 0%, #d4ecf4 100%);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #0077b6;
  }

  .info-callout h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #0077b6;
  }

  .info-callout h4 i {
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
  }

  .info-callout p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
